---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Groundspeed Labs"
  description="Groundspeed Labs builds practical mobile tools. Current product: KeepValid, a document expiry reminder app."
  contentMode="wide"
>
  <section class="home-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Practical mobile tools</p>

    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="hero-kicker">Groundspeed Labs / mobile utilities / current product</p>
        <h1>Keep important documents from expiring quietly.</h1>
        <p class="tagline">
          KeepValid helps people stay ahead of expiring documents without adding
          more admin to their day.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-summary">
          Track passports, licenses, IDs, cards, and other deadline-sensitive
          documents from your phone. KeepValid is designed for anyone managing
          multiple expirations and especially useful when missing one has real
          consequences.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero-panel" aria-label="Current product">
        <p class="panel-label">Current product</p>
        <h2>KeepValid</h2>
        <p class="panel-copy">
          Track important documents before they turn into blocked renewals,
          missed plans, or last-minute scrambles.
        </p>

        <ul class="signal-list">
          <li>Scan or add a document in seconds</li>
          <li>See what expires this year at a glance</li>
          <li>Get reminded by push or email before it becomes a problem</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="/keepvalid/#updates" class="cta">Get updates</a>

        <a href="/keepvalid/" class="app-card compact">
          <span class="app-card-label">See product page</span>
          <h3>KeepValid <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></h3>
          <p>Document expiry tracking for mobile.</p>
        </a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="home-principles" aria-labelledby="how-we-build">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="section-label">How we build</p>
      <h2 id="how-we-build">Small scope. Clear utility. Mobile first.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="principles-grid">
      <article class="principle-card">
        <p class="principle-index">01</p>
        <h3>One clear job</h3>
        <p>
          Each app should solve a specific problem cleanly instead of turning
          into a bundle of half-related features.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="principle-card">
        <p class="principle-index">02</p>
        <h3>Useful on the device</h3>
        <p>
          Mobile is the product surface. We bias toward flows that are quick,
          practical, and comfortable to use from the phone itself.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="principle-card">
        <p class="principle-index">03</p>
        <h3>Less noise, more signal</h3>
        <p>
          The software should explain itself quickly, keep maintenance low, and
          avoid the usual layer of unnecessary complexity.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
